# Accessibility Guide

This application includes comprehensive accessibility (a11y) tools and utilities to ensure your app is usable by everyone.

## 🛠️ Included Tools

### 1. **Axe-core** - Automated Accessibility Testing
- Automatically tests your app for WCAG violations in development
- Reports issues directly in the browser console
- Supports WCAG 2.0, 2.1, and Section 508 standards

### 2. **ESLint Plugin JSX A11y** - Static Analysis
- Lints your JSX for accessibility issues
- Catches common mistakes during development
- Integrated with your existing ESLint setup

### 3. **Accessible Components** - Pre-built Helpers
- SkipLink - Skip to main content
- LiveRegion - Screen reader announcements
- VisuallyHidden - Hide visually, keep accessible
- FocusTrap - Trap focus for modals/dialogs

### 4. **Utility Functions** - A11y Helpers
- announceToScreenReader()
- trapFocus()
- generateA11yId()
- prefersReducedMotion()

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Using Axe-core

In your `main.tsx` or `index.tsx`:

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import ReactDOM from 'react-dom/client';
import App from './app/app';
import { initializeAxe } from './utils/axe-helper';

// Initialize axe for development
if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {
  initializeAxe(React, ReactDOM, 1000);
}

const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!);
root.render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <App />
  </React.StrictMode>
);
```

### Using Accessible Components

```tsx
import { 
  SkipLink, 
  LiveRegion, 
  VisuallyHidden, 
  FocusTrap 
} from './components/A11yComponents';

function App() {
  return (
    <>
      <SkipLink targetId="main-content" />
      
      <nav>
        {/* Navigation */}
      </nav>
      
      <main id="main-content">
        <h1>
          Page Title
          <VisuallyHidden> - Accessible subtitle</VisuallyHidden>
        </h1>
        
        <LiveRegion message="Data loaded successfully" />
      </main>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Using Focus Trap (for Modals)

```tsx
import { FocusTrap } from './components/A11yComponents';

function Modal({ isOpen, onClose }) {
  if (!isOpen) return null;
  
  return (
    <div className="modal-overlay">
      <FocusTrap active={isOpen}>
        <div 
          role="dialog" 
          aria-modal="true"
          aria-labelledby="modal-title"
        >
          <h2 id="modal-title">Modal Title</h2>
          <p>Modal content</p>
          <button onClick={onClose}>Close</button>
        </div>
      </FocusTrap>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## 📋 Best Practices

### 1. Semantic HTML

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Semantic
<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/home">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

// ❌ Bad - Not semantic
<div className="nav">
  <div onClick={goHome}>Home</div>
</div>
```

### 2. ARIA Labels

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Descriptive label
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <Icon name="close" />
</button>

// ❌ Bad - No label for icon-only button
<button>
  <Icon name="close" />
</button>
```

### 3. Form Labels

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Label associated with input
<label htmlFor="email">Email Address</label>
<input id="email" type="email" name="email" />

// ❌ Bad - No label
<input type="email" placeholder="Email" />
```

### 4. Keyboard Navigation

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Keyboard accessible
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click Me</button>

// ❌ Bad - Not keyboard accessible
<div onClick={handleClick}>Click Me</div>
```

### 5. Alt Text for Images

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Descriptive alt text
<img src="logo.png" alt="Company Name Logo" />

// ✅ Good - Decorative image
<img src="decoration.png" alt="" role="presentation" />

// ❌ Bad - Missing alt text
<img src="logo.png" />
```

## 🔍 Testing Accessibility

### Automated Testing with Axe

```typescript
import { runA11yCheck, axeConfigs } from './utils/axe-helper';

// Test entire page
const results = await runA11yCheck();

// Test specific element
const element = document.getElementById('my-component');
const results = await runA11yCheck(element);

// Test with WCAG 2.1 AA standard
const results = await runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.wcag21aa);
```

### Manual Testing Checklist

- [ ] Can you navigate the entire site using only keyboard?
- [ ] Does Tab key move focus in logical order?
- [ ] Are focus indicators clearly visible?
- [ ] Can you skip to main content?
- [ ] Do all images have appropriate alt text?
- [ ] Are form fields properly labeled?
- [ ] Do buttons and links have descriptive text?
- [ ] Is color contrast sufficient (4.5:1 for normal text)?
- [ ] Does the site work with screen readers?
- [ ] Are error messages announced to screen readers?

## 🎨 Accessible Styling

### Focus Indicators

```css
/* Ensure visible focus indicators */
button:focus,
a:focus,
input:focus {
  outline: 2px solid #4A90E2;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Don't remove outline without replacement */
button:focus {
  outline: none; /* ❌ Bad */
}

button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #4A90E2; /* ✅ Good */
}
```

### Color Contrast

```css
/* ✅ Good - 4.5:1 contrast ratio */
.text {
  color: #333333;
  background-color: #FFFFFF;
}

/* ❌ Bad - Insufficient contrast */
.text {
  color: #CCCCCC;
  background-color: #FFFFFF;
}
```

### Reduced Motion

```css
/* Respect user preference for reduced motion */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## 🛡️ ARIA Roles and Properties

### Common ARIA Roles

```tsx
// Navigation
<nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">

// Main content
<main role="main" id="main-content">

// Search
<form role="search">

// Alert
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">

// Dialog
<div role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">

// Button (when not using <button>)
<div role="button" tabIndex={0} onClick={handleClick} onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}>
```

### ARIA States and Properties

```tsx
// Expanded/Collapsed
<button aria-expanded={isOpen}>Toggle Menu</button>

// Current page
<a href="/home" aria-current="page">Home</a>

// Required field
<input required aria-required="true" />

// Invalid field
<input aria-invalid="true" aria-describedby="error-message" />
<span id="error-message">Please enter a valid email</span>

// Disabled state
<button disabled aria-disabled="true">Submit</button>

// Loading state
<button aria-busy="true">Loading...</button>

// Hidden content
<div aria-hidden="true">Decorative content</div>
```

## 📊 Axe Configuration

### WCAG Levels

```typescript
import { runA11yCheck, axeConfigs } from './utils/axe-helper';

// WCAG 2.0 Level A (minimum)
runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.wcag2a);

// WCAG 2.0 Level AA (recommended)
runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.wcag2aa);

// WCAG 2.1 Level AA (modern standard)
runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.wcag21aa);

// Section 508 (US government)
runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.section508);

// Best practices
runA11yCheck(null, axeConfigs.bestPractice);
```

### Custom Configuration

```typescript
const customConfig = {
  runOnly: {
    type: 'tag',
    values: ['wcag2a', 'wcag2aa', 'best-practice']
  },
  rules: {
    'color-contrast': { enabled: true },
    'image-alt': { enabled: true },
    'label': { enabled: true }
  }
};

runA11yCheck(null, customConfig);
```

## 🔧 Utility Functions

### Announce to Screen Reader

```typescript
import { announceToScreenReader } from './utils/a11y-utils';

// Polite announcement (doesn't interrupt)
announceToScreenReader('Data loaded successfully', 'polite');

// Assertive announcement (interrupts current reading)
announceToScreenReader('Error: Please try again', 'assertive');
```

### Check for Reduced Motion

```typescript
import { prefersReducedMotion } from './utils/a11y-utils';

if (!prefersReducedMotion()) {
  // Play animations
  element.classList.add('animate');
}
```

### Generate Unique IDs

```typescript
import { generateA11yId } from './utils/a11y-utils';

const labelId = generateA11yId('label');
const descriptionId = generateA11yId('description');

<label id={labelId}>Email</label>
<input aria-labelledby={labelId} aria-describedby={descriptionId} />
<span id={descriptionId}>We'll never share your email</span>
```

