## 🎯 Common Violations and Fixes

### Missing Alt Text

```tsx
// ❌ Violation
<img src="photo.jpg" />

// ✅ Fix
<img src="photo.jpg" alt="Description of photo" />
```

### Missing Form Labels

```tsx
// ❌ Violation
<input type="text" />

// ✅ Fix
<label htmlFor="name">Name</label>
<input id="name" type="text" />
```

### Insufficient Color Contrast

```tsx
// ❌ Violation
<p style={{ color: '#ccc', background: '#fff' }}>Text</p>

// ✅ Fix
<p style={{ color: '#333', background: '#fff' }}>Text</p>
```

### Non-Keyboard Accessible Elements

```tsx
// ❌ Violation
<div onClick={handleClick}>Click me</div>

// ✅ Fix
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
```

---

**Remember**: Accessibility is not optional. It's a fundamental requirement for building inclusive web applications that everyone can use.

For questions or issues, consult the [WCAG Guidelines](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/) or run axe tests to identify specific problems.
